FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1779069821
OL,3,CBurnham seeks to reassure markets but
OL,4,Ckeeps room to bend the rules
OL,6,FHe seems to be signalling to investors
OL,7,F- on whom the UK government relies to
OL,8,Ffinance its spending - that he would
OL,9,Fbe disciplined if he became PM, while
OL,10,Falso leaving himself some room to
OL,11,Ftweak the rules, allowing for higher
OL,12,Finvestment or more time to meet debt
OL,13,Ftargets.
OL,15,FThe UK's national debt has risen
OL,16,Fsubstantially over the last 20 years,
OL,17,Fand investors are demanding higher
OL,18,Freturns to lend to the government -
OL,19,Fpushing up costs for households and
OL,20,Fbusinesses too.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
