OL,3,CBurnham seeks to reassure markets but
OL,4,Ckeeps room to bend the rules
OL,6,FBurnham's critics seek to portray him
OL,7,Fas a liability - even a "Liz Truss
OL,8,Fmark 2". Burnham argues his comments
OL,9,Flast year about the UK being "in hock"
OL,10,Fto bond markets were not about
OL,11,Fignoring investors, but about ensuring
OL,12,Fthe country is governed well enough
OL,13,Fnot to be constantly on the brink of
OL,14,Fcrisis.
