OL,3,CBurnham seeks to reassure markets but
OL,4,Ckeeps room to bend the rules
OL,6,FOn the EU, he says there is a "long-
OL,7,Fterm" case for rejoining but that he
OL,8,Fwon't be "advocating" it in this by-
OL,9,Felection - implying he would stick to
OL,10,FLabour's current manifesto red lines
OL,11,Fin this parliament (no return to the
OL,12,Fsingle market, customs union or free
OL,13,Fmovement).
OL,15,FThe prospect of "fiscal slippage" may
OL,16,Fnot cut through in Makerfield, but
OL,17,Fmortgage rates and economic
OL,18,Fcredibility will.
OL,26,@nD@_OUoD@EO]pD@JOUpD@UO]wD@QOUwD@aO]
